# Orchestrator delegation

**Default:** work directly.

**`/orchestrate`** (see **`.cursor/agents/orchestrate.md`**):

- **Interview-first:** ask clarifying questions before big plans or delegation when anything is unclear; **no full plan** until resolved or the user waives; **suggestions** (options/trade-offs) encouraged.
- **Orchestrator** picks which **Task** subagents to run and when. **Skills** from **`.cursor/skills/`** on demand. **No MCP** unless the project added it ‚Äî use **CLI** (`git`, `gh`, package managers, project scripts).
- **Git gate:** **Never** `git commit`, `git push`, or remote-affecting **merge** without **explicit user approval** after showing exact commands (all agents, including **`/orchestrate`** after review).
- **Models:** YAML **`model:`** is a hint (**`orchestrate`** ‚Üí Opus, **`coder`** / **`code-review`** / **`verifier`** ‚Üí Sonnet when available). Use **Haiku / Sonnet / Opus / Composer** or other tiers the product exposes; if paid tier is exhausted, use **Composer** or a **free** model **adequate** for the step (**`AGENTS.md`**).
- **Pauses:** After **`coder`** (optional) ‚Äî default wait before **`code-review`**. After **`code-review`** ‚Äî **stop** (no verifier / merge in the same turn); continue with a new message when ready.
- **Large tasks / milestones:** **feature branch** from **`development`** in the **same** working copy; see **`orchestrate.md`** ‚Äî Git model.
- **Delegation:** **Task `coder`** ‚Üí **Task `code-review`** ‚Üí **ask approval** ‚Üí commit/push ‚Üí **ask approval** ‚Üí **merge feature ‚Üí `development`** when **READY** and **after** Pause C **and** approvals. No **`glab`/`gh` MR`** ‚Äî local **`git`** per **`orchestrate.md`**.
- **Optional (after interview):** **`code-explorer`** (‚Äúhow X works‚Äù / deep trace), **`code-architect`** (design / trade-offs), or the **`codebase-explore`** skill (broad read-only map) when relevant ‚Äî **one** recon path by default; see **`orchestrate.md`**.

Add optional skills under **`.cursor/skills/`** when you need them (debugger, deploy).

Suggest **`/orchestrate`** for large tasks; ask first if unclear.
